Class PropertyMapperVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.geotools.filter.visitor.DuplicatingFilterVisitor
      • org.codice.ddf.spatial.ogc.csw.catalog.common.PropertyMapperVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.opengis.filter.expression.ExpressionVisitor, org.opengis.filter.FilterVisitor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ECQLMapperVisitor

    public class PropertyMapperVisitor
extends org.geotools.filter.visitor.DuplicatingFilterVisitor
    This Visitor creates a new Filter with the PropertyNames remapped as defined in the passed in Map. If a given property name doesn't exist in the map it remains unchanged. For example if you pass in a map with key->key1 value->key2 and run it on a filter like `key1 = 10 AND key3 = 20` the resulting filter will be `key2 = 10 AND key3 = 20`
